<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880314-0068 </DOCNO><HL> Former Merchant Banker Meets Bail in Guinness Case </HL><SO> </SO><CO> EUROP </CO><IN> SCR </IN><DATELINE> LONDON   </DATELINE><TEXT>   A British magistrate freed Lord Spens on #500,000 ($924,000) bail after the former director of the merchant bank Henry Ansbacher andamp; Co. was charged with offenses related to Guinness PLC's 1986 takeover of Distillers Co.    Lord Spens was ordered to appear in court on April 12 with four others charged so far in the Guinness affair. He was told not to contact current employees of the Ansbacher group.    As previously reported, Lord Spens was charged Thursday with falsifying documents related to the purchase of Guinness shares during the Distillers bid and conspiring to create a false market in Guinness shares. </TEXT></DOC>